\subsection{Summary: Emergent Gravity}

We have demonstrated that:

\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{The metric tensor is emergent}: Defined as a bilinear functional of $\Theta$ and its derivatives, not postulated as fundamental.
    
    \item \textbf{Curvature arises from phase gradients}: Standard geometric structures (Christoffel symbols, Riemann tensor, Ricci tensor) are computed from the emergent metric.
    
    \item \textbf{Einstein equation is derived}: The field equation $G_{\mu\nu} = \kappa T^{(\Theta)}_{\mu\nu}$ emerges from $\Theta$-dynamics, not assumed.
    
    \item \textbf{Classical GR is recovered}: In the limit of slowly varying phase and suppressed diffusion, we exactly reproduce Einstein's General Relativity.
    
    \item \textbf{Diffeomorphism invariance is preserved}: The emergent framework respects general covariance.
\end{enumerate}

This establishes gravity as an \textit{effective} rather than \textit{fundamental} interaction, resolving the quantization problem and providing a pathway to quantum gravity through the underlying $\Theta$-field theory.

